What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Retail Cloud Market?



Market Analysis and Insights

Global Retail Cloud Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the retail cloud market will exhibit a CAGR of 19.2% for the forecast period of 2022-2029 and is expected to reach the market value of USD 73.44 billion by 2029.

To gain a competitive advantage in terms of speed and agility, retail organizations and retailers can migrate their business applications and infrastructure resources to cloud service architectures such as Software as a Service (SaaS), Platform as a Service (PaaS), and Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS). Cloud computing features are appealing and becoming increasingly relevant in the retail industry for activities such as Supply Chain Management (SCM), customer management, merchandising, and workforce management. The cloud's strengths and capabilities are rapidly changing the retail landscape by providing a variety of benefits such as cost savings, usage-based billing, and business continuity and agility.

The rising demands for smartphones, the growing need for compliance and collaboration, and the shift to an omni-channel experience are all expected to boost the growth of the retail cloud market during the forecast period. On the other hand, rising mobile point of sale in the market, as well as rising click and collect programmes, will boost various opportunities, leading to the growth of the retail cloud market during the forecast period.

The impact on retail cloud varies according to demand from various industries. For example, the electronics and fashion industries have been hard hit by low demand, whereas food, household goods, and pharmaceuticals have seen a drastic shift in demand and are thus looking for Omni channel presence, which is further boosting retail cloud demand. The market is expected to grow rapidly during the forecast period as a result of the advantages it provides over traditional retail.

However, privacy and security concerns, as well as shifting consumer preferences, are acting as market restraints for retail cloud during the forecasted period.

